#: ../../../system/arm/xlnx-zynq.rst:2
msgid "Xilinx Zynq board (``xilinx-zynq-a9``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/xlnx-zynq.rst:3
msgid ""
"The Zynq 7000 family is based on the AMD SoC architecture. These products "
"integrate a feature-rich dual or single-core Arm Cortex-A9 MPCore based "
"processing system (PS) and AMD programmable logic (PL) in a single device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/arm/xlnx-zynq.rst:7
msgid ""
"The SoC is documented in the `Zynq 7000 Technical Reference manual <https://"
"docs.amd.com/r/en-US/ug585-zynq-7000-SoC-TRM/Zynq-7000-SoC-Technical-"
"Reference-Manual>`__."
msgstr ""

